WEBVTT

00:00.024 --> 00:01.492
<i>Previously on "Suits"...</i>

00:01.527 --> 00:02.931
I've been after Sutter
for three years now.

00:02.932 --> 00:04.466
This guy's one
slippery son of a bitch.

00:04.566 --> 00:06.265
Wait a second, William Sutter?

00:06.301 --> 00:08.034
He came to me a week ago
to take him on.

00:08.069 --> 00:09.780
You cross one line
that puts me in jeopardy,

00:09.804 --> 00:11.282
I'm gonna pull the plug
on this whole thing.

00:11.306 --> 00:13.573
I need a large,
expensive home in the Hamptons.

00:13.751 --> 00:15.284
Why are you buying
a vacation home?

00:15.365 --> 00:16.598
Because I told Tara Messer

00:16.633 --> 00:17.677
that I have
a property out there,

00:17.701 --> 00:19.012
and I hired her
to remodel it for me.

00:19.036 --> 00:20.835
Damn it, Harvey,
I'm not colluding on this,

00:20.871 --> 00:22.115
and you're in here
trying to get me

00:22.139 --> 00:23.916
to bring an indictment
against your own client.

00:23.940 --> 00:25.818
Because when you bring that
indictment, I'm gonna beat it,

00:25.842 --> 00:27.108
and if you don't bring it,

00:27.144 --> 00:29.322
and continue investigating
my client, I'm gonna sue you.

00:29.346 --> 00:30.523
I think it's pretty
goddamn funny

00:30.547 --> 00:31.858
that you don't trust me,
when you're the one

00:31.882 --> 00:33.762
that won't even tell me
what you're in here for.

00:33.820 --> 00:36.940
Okay.
I'll do it.

00:36.941 --> 00:38.807
- Excuse me?
- Your pro Bono.

00:38.843 --> 00:40.476
Bring me the file
tomorrow morning.

00:40.511 --> 00:42.077
It was a good fix, Sean.

00:42.113 --> 00:44.513
- It was a good move, Harvey.
- Want to get a drink?

00:44.548 --> 00:45.914
- Why don't we just
have one here?

00:45.950 --> 00:47.082
Why?
As of right now,

00:47.118 --> 00:48.695
you have no action
pending against my client.

00:48.719 --> 00:51.020
But as of tomorrow, I do,

00:51.055 --> 00:53.355
'cause those indictments
are coming down in the morning.

00:53.391 --> 00:55.924
- Kevin, what did you do?
- I got in a fight with my wife.

00:56.143 --> 00:59.778
I got drunk. I got into my car,
and I almost killed someone.

00:59.813 --> 01:03.281
I'm missing 1,000 chances
to hug my kids in the morning

01:03.317 --> 01:05.050
and kiss my wife good night,

01:05.084 --> 01:07.953
all because I couldn't
control myself.

01:07.988 --> 01:09.921
What were you fighting
with your wife about?

01:09.957 --> 01:13.391
I can't.
I just can't.

01:15.995 --> 01:17.962
[door buzzes]

01:24.403 --> 01:27.571
Harvey.
What are you doing here?

01:27.607 --> 01:30.507
Mike, sit down.
I need to tell you something.

01:32.011 --> 01:33.744
What's going on?

01:33.779 --> 01:35.713
I'm working on getting
you out of here.

01:35.748 --> 01:37.381
Yeah, I know you are.

01:37.416 --> 01:38.861
I'm not talking about
what we're doing for Cahill.

01:38.885 --> 01:39.995
I'm talking about
something else.

01:40.019 --> 01:41.129
Harvey, we're in a room
full of people.

01:41.153 --> 01:42.486
You can't be talking
about Cahill.

01:42.521 --> 01:43.721
If Kevin finds out--

01:43.756 --> 01:45.200
It doesn't matter
if Kevin finds out now.

01:45.224 --> 01:46.457
He's done.

01:46.492 --> 01:48.225
What do you mean, "He's done?"

01:48.261 --> 01:52.196
I mean Rachel's dead...

01:52.231 --> 01:54.365
and Kevin killed her.

01:54.700 --> 01:57.234
<i>[tense music]</i>

01:57.269 --> 01:58.602
What?

01:58.637 --> 02:00.571
It's true.

02:00.606 --> 02:01.538
You son of a bitch.

02:01.574 --> 02:02.606
You're lying to me.

02:02.641 --> 02:04.608
Goddamn it.
He told you he did it.

02:04.862 --> 02:07.062
- Bullshit.
- He got drunk.

02:07.098 --> 02:08.798
He got in a car.

02:08.833 --> 02:10.399
He murdered the woman you love.

02:10.435 --> 02:12.201
- Stop saying that.
- And now you're going

02:12.236 --> 02:14.703
to be stuck in here with him
for the rest of your life.

02:14.739 --> 02:16.439
Stop it.
Kevin would never do that to me.

02:16.474 --> 02:17.606
- Mike, wake up.
- No.

02:17.642 --> 02:18.607
- Mike.
- No.

02:18.643 --> 02:19.975
- Wake up. Wake up.
- No!

02:20.011 --> 02:23.078
- Mike, wake up.
- No, no, no, no, no.

02:23.114 --> 02:25.448
Mike, wake up.

02:26.083 --> 02:27.816
[heavy breathing]

02:27.851 --> 02:31.219
Hey, you okay?

02:31.255 --> 02:33.055
- Yeah. Yeah, I'm fine.
- You sure?

02:33.090 --> 02:34.567
'Cause that was some dream
you were having.

02:34.591 --> 02:38.026
I'm fine.

02:38.062 --> 02:42.664
Just going back to sleep.

02:49.239 --> 02:51.172
[elevator dings]

02:54.177 --> 02:56.444
Harvey, good,
there you are.

02:56.479 --> 02:58.146
- What's going on?
- Sutter just called.

02:58.181 --> 02:59.725
Let me guess,
the indictments came down?

02:59.749 --> 03:01.382
He wants you in his office
an hour ago.

03:01.418 --> 03:02.495
I'll tell him
you're on your way.

03:02.519 --> 03:05.353
No.
Tell him you couldn't reach me.

03:05.388 --> 03:07.188
You want him to start
sweating, but why?

03:07.223 --> 03:08.568
Because when people
start sweating,

03:08.592 --> 03:11.826
they start talking
to their lawyer.

03:12.161 --> 03:13.628
I'll tell Ray to be on hold.

03:13.663 --> 03:15.329
No, tell him to pull around.

03:15.365 --> 03:16.976
But you just said you weren't
going to Sutter's.

03:17.000 --> 03:19.400
I'm not.
I'm going somewhere else.

03:19.735 --> 03:23.237
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:23.272 --> 03:24.783
Oh, look who it is,
the man of the hour.

03:24.807 --> 03:27.241
Did you get my indictments?
I sure as hell did.

03:27.276 --> 03:28.442
Now that the party's started,

03:28.477 --> 03:30.411
why don't you tell me
what Kevin Miller knows?

03:30.446 --> 03:32.291
- What are you talking about?
- You went after the guy

03:32.315 --> 03:34.030
to try to get him
to flip on Sutter,

03:34.130 --> 03:35.641
so what'd you think
he was gonna give you?

03:35.665 --> 03:37.398
- I'm not gonna tell you that.
- Why not?

03:37.433 --> 03:38.844
- Because I told you
when I started this thing,

03:38.868 --> 03:40.968
I'm not gonna collude.
We're not colluding.

03:41.003 --> 03:42.436
It's called discovery.

03:42.471 --> 03:46.540
So why don't you tell me what
the hell Kevin Miller knows?

03:47.577 --> 03:49.243
He developed
the trading programs

03:49.278 --> 03:52.485
that Sutter claims to use
to get his superior returns.

03:52.586 --> 03:53.997
Then that program's got
to be full of shit,

03:54.021 --> 03:55.087
because if it isn't--

03:55.122 --> 03:56.054
Then Sutter's not
inside trading,

03:56.090 --> 03:57.289
which he sure as shit is.

03:57.324 --> 03:58.991
So you're looking to have
Kevin testify

03:59.026 --> 04:01.526
that software is bullshit,
and Sutter knows it.

04:01.562 --> 04:03.161
- Bingo.
- Then let me ask you this,

04:03.197 --> 04:05.497
what exactly did you
put Kevin away for?

04:05.532 --> 04:06.643
And why do you need
to know that?

04:06.667 --> 04:07.978
Because it might help us
figure out

04:08.002 --> 04:09.568
what his weak spot is.

04:10.154 --> 04:11.554
We got him on
vehicular assault

04:11.589 --> 04:13.823
while driving
under the influence.

04:13.859 --> 04:15.358
Are you kidding me?

04:15.393 --> 04:16.992
Why didn't you think
to tell us that?

04:17.029 --> 04:18.295
Why would I?

04:18.329 --> 04:20.696
Mike's parents were killed
by a drunk driver.

04:20.732 --> 04:21.910
And how the hell
was I supposed to know that?

04:21.934 --> 04:23.374
I don't know.
It would have been nice

04:23.402 --> 04:24.634
to know what this asshole did,

04:24.670 --> 04:27.871
before we sent Mike
back into a cell with him.

04:27.906 --> 04:32.242
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:33.579 --> 04:36.646
Hey, what happened
to you this morning?

04:36.682 --> 04:38.114
What do you mean?

04:38.810 --> 04:42.211
- You skipped breakfast.
- I wasn't hungry.

04:42.247 --> 04:45.348
- That all it was?
- What are you talking about?

04:45.383 --> 04:47.283
- Come on, Mike, you had
a nightmare last night.

04:47.318 --> 04:48.751
You've been avoiding me
all morning,

04:48.786 --> 04:50.598
and you're acting weird
right now--what's going on?

04:50.622 --> 04:53.623
Nothing's going on.

04:53.658 --> 04:55.336
Then why the hell were you
in a cold sweat,

04:55.360 --> 04:57.360
muttering something about
someone not finding out,

04:57.395 --> 05:00.296
and then calling out
my name?

05:00.331 --> 05:01.764
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:01.799 --> 05:04.700
All right, Kevin, you want
to know what's going on?

05:04.914 --> 05:07.881
I had a dream that you
killed Rachel in a car accident.

05:07.917 --> 05:09.883
That's probably why
I don't particularly feel

05:09.919 --> 05:11.262
like hanging out
with you this morning.

05:11.286 --> 05:12.997
Because of what you told me
about your parents, Mike,

05:13.021 --> 05:15.722
I'm really sorry.
Are you?

05:15.757 --> 05:17.101
What--what's that
supposed to mean?

05:17.125 --> 05:18.502
I mean, last night you told me
you almost killed someone.

05:18.526 --> 05:21.027
Are you sorry about that?
You got to be kidding me.

05:21.062 --> 05:22.506
You have a dream,
and now you're questioning

05:22.530 --> 05:24.170
if I feel bad
about what I did that night?

05:24.199 --> 05:26.010
You still haven't answered
whether or not you do.

05:26.034 --> 05:27.311
You know what?
You need to be pissed off

05:27.335 --> 05:29.268
at me to deal with your shit,
you go right ahead.

05:29.304 --> 05:31.248
But I feel horrible about
what happened that night,

05:31.272 --> 05:32.505
and for your information,

05:32.540 --> 05:34.741
the guy that I hit
is fully recovered right now,

05:34.776 --> 05:39.312
and I'm still in here
paying for this shit.

05:39.313 --> 05:42.613
<b><font color="#00FF00">♪ Suits 6x06 ♪</font></b>
<font color="#00FFFF">Spain</font>
